cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.CE, cs.NE, cs.LG

The paper proposes a power-efficient approach for implementing deep neural networks (DNNs) through low-power analog circuits. This topic falls under the category of "Emerging Technologies" (cs.ET) as it explores a new approach to hardware implementation of AI. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Deep Learning to compensate for device mismatch effects, which is related to "Computer Architecture" (cs.AR) and "Circuit Design" (cs.CE). The focus on DNNs also suggests a connection to "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE), and the use of constraints in the training process is related to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG).
